midmarch and invited nakayama to visit moscow afterwards the 
official said 
to date four japanese prime ministers have visited moscow but 
no soviet leaders has ever visited tokyo 
japan has repeatedly requested the soviet union to send its top 
leader to japan to improve relations 
the tokyo government hopes a visit by a soviet leader would help 
resolve the territorial dispute over the northern territories 
a group of small islands off northern japan claimed by japan but 
occupied by the soviet union 
the two countries began longstalled talks on a peace treaty 
earlier this year but the territorial issue remains the largest 
stumbling block 
