<TEXT>
the number of legal abortions performed in the 
united states has held largely steady throughout the 1980s us 
health officials said thursday 
a total of 1353671 legal abortions were performed in the 
united states in 1987 an increase of just under 2 percent from 
1328112 in 1986 the national centers for disease control said in 
its weekly report 
the total compares with 1297606 in 1980 and 1333521 in 1984 
the actual number has risen somewhat as has the us 
population since 1980 but the rate of abortions has fallen 
slightly in 1987 health officials reported 356 abortions for 
every 1000 live births compared to 359 in 1980 the atlantabased 
cdc said 
twentysix percent of the women having abortions in 1987 the 
latest year for which statistics are available were under 20 
thirtythree percent were 2024 and 41 percent were 25 or older 
seventythree percent were unmarried and 54 percent had never 
given birth 
