<TEXT>
the death of former philippine president 
ferdinand e marcos today leaves his wife alone to battle charges 
they stole between 168 million and 10 billion from their 
homelands treasury 
a federal indictment charges that 60yearold imelda marcos and 
her husband took 168 million 
but the philippine government accuses the couple in a lawsuit of 
making off with between 35 billion and 10 billion in cash and 
property while his country amassed a large foreign debt 
the money allegedly was spent directly or indirectly on such 
luxuries as prime new york city real estate a 4 million home in 
beverly hills and paintings by artists including picasso van gogh 
and jan bruegel 
as the marcoses fled to the united states on feb 26 1986 the 
customs service impounded more than 7 million in cash valuables 
and jewelry from their plane 
his 20year rule came to a swift end in a public uprising after 
he was accused of stealing an election from corazon aquino now the 
philippine president 
marcos entered a honolulu hospital jan 16 with bronchial 
asthma pneumonia and congestive heart failure he died there this 
morning 
mrs marcos pleaded innocent to the federal charges her 
husbands ill health kept him from making the trip from hawaii to 
new york for arraignment on racketeering and other charges 
the federal grand jury that indicted the marcoses last october 
also indicted adnan khashoggi 54 the flamboyant saudi financier 
once reputed to be the worlds wealthiest man he was arrested in 
switzerland and extradited to new york 
khashoggi is accused of helping hide riches stolen by the 
marcoses and taking away 25 paintings from new york properties 
owned by the couple and later selling them for 32 million 
although marcos never appeared in court to counter the charges 
directly he commented when reports surfaced in late 1987 that a 
federal investigation was under way into his real estate dealings 
and jewelry acquisitions 
he called the investigation a clear case of pure harassment 
he said he and his wife committed no wrongdoings no violation 
of any law in our conduct in relation to any properties now alleged 
to be illegally obtained by us from anyone 
us prosecutors this year conceded marcos was too ill to stand 
trial and his case was severed from the others but the charges were 
not dropped 
the aquino government sought 50 billion in punitive damages in 
a lawsuit filed in federal court in california against the marcoses 
and an aide ramon azurin 
the marcoses were accused in the lawsuit of bribery extortion 
theft and other charges in a scheme to steal billions of dollars in 
public money to be used for their personal benefit 
the aquino government says it has statements from swiss bank 
authorities that marcos and his family have accounts there worth 
more than 15 billion 
a federal judges order bars the marcoses from using any of 
their assets except to pay their lawyers and for daily living 
expenses mrs marcos has complained that this restriction has left 
her in poverty 
</TEXT>
