police mediated a truce between armed 
residents of a drugridden neighborhood and alleged crack cocaine 
dealers after simmering tensions erupted into a crossstreet 
gunbattle officers said thursday 
the truce in which neighbors agreed to put firearms away and 
drug dealers agreed to keep dealing off the street has brought a 
measure of calm to the nervous hilltop neighborhood 
police said the two sides exchanged 300 shots saturday during an 
antidrug block party at the home of army ranger staff sgt bill 
foulk who summoned 11 offduty rangers as reinforcements 
no one was injured however until the next day when fistfights 
broke out and some neighbors suffered scrapes and bruises from 
thrown bricks only two arrests were made saturday both of alleged 
