<TEXT>
when 10yearold joshua dennis was rescued 
from an abandoned mine after five days he had long since exhausted 
his tiny supply of licorice but thought hed been missing only a 
couple of days 
mostly i just slept a lot of the time i got tired of looking 
around and just sat there the boy said thursday i wasnt 
feeling very lonely or scared but i cried once 
his feet mottled purple with mild frostbite and propped on a 
pillow joshua spoke from his hospital bed just 24 hours after 
rescuers found him on a ledge some 2000 feet inside the mine where 
he got lost during a scouting expedition 
i was just following the wall after being separated from 
his father inside the mine last friday night he said there was 
a whole bunch of exits and i went down the wrong one 
joshua is in good condition and expected to go home to suburban 
kearns over the weekend his doctor at primary childrens medical 
center said 
hes squared away hell do just fine dr ted jenkins 
said 
the boys father terry dennis said joshua went into the hidden 
treasure mine with 10 bitesize pieces of licorice in his pocket 
he exhausted the meager cache only after slowly sucking one piece 
at a time he had no water and was dehydrated when found wednesday 
afternoon 
joshua cub scout strayed from the boy scout group his father 
was helping supervise on an expedition into the former silver lead 
and zinc mine in the oquirrh mountains 45 miles southwest of salt 
lake city 
after five days hope had all but vanished that the boy would be 
found alive then a search team that had passed within 150 feet of 
him in half a dozen sweeps heard his faint cry and discovered him 
on the ledge 
joshua said that during his vigil he had heard searchers voices 
a few times but his cries for help werent heard 
i wondered how long it was going to take me to find my way 
out he said i couldnt really hear what they were saying i 
called for help but not one of the times they couldnt hear me 
at the head of his bed was a white hard hat inscribed with the 
names of the two utah power amp light co mine rescue team members 
who found him 
i was thinking if it was day or night or what day it was i 
thought it was night and when they told me it was wednesday i 
thought it was sunday joshua said 
