and it is so horrifying to see the results of this rampant gimme 
gimme economy she said 
im really trying to look at that from a few different angles 
im in the midst of redefining the introduction it is places that 
ive shot pictures of mostly in downtown new york theyre not 
exactly ruins but they look like it 
that has been one of the nicest things about working on this 
piece anderson said i go out at night a lot real late and 
shoot a lot of places ive shot thousands of things for this 
piece slides moving images and films that were sent through a 
visual digital computer and look very grainy its a beautiful look 
stories work so much better at night and these arent exactly 
bedtime stories i find some of them kind of horrifying people 
have drifted into the shots its a whole different world from 
midnight on out there its making me feel at home in new york in a 
way i never have before 
the show also has some cheery animation i was trying to make 
a real cartoon with all these screens i thought i need some 
disneytype bluebirds bluebirds make me happy i drew them on the 
computer with picket fences and roses there are songs about 
utopia 
are they ironic 
some of them are some arent she replied irony is a 
really tricky thing i try to use irony sparingly im doing a lot 
more singing in this show i find i can say ironic things but i 
cant sing ironic things 
the other big difference in this show is that ive been taking 
singing lessons three years this is the first performance where 
im trying to use that to my shock i discovered i was a soprano i 
thought id be a low alto when you sing high its a very 
vulnerable feeling and you really have to believe what youre 
singing thats not to say some of these songs arent silly and 
preposterous 
there are fewer computerized filters changing my voice im 
trying very hard to be truthful sometimes thats not very clever 
and i dont mind that its not these things dont have triple and 
quadruple meanings they have one meaning 
anderson performed her sixhour united states parts i iv 
at the 1983 next wave festival her last big performing tour was in 
1986 
