<TEXT>
former corporate raider paul a bilzerian 
received the stiffest sentence yet in the governments threeyear 
corruption probe but a federal judge said it wont necessarily 
deter other financial crimes 
i have been around the criminal justice system for 40 years 
us district judge robert j ward said wednesday before sentencing 
bilzerian to four years in jail and a 15 million fine 
when i began my experience there were wheelerdealers he 
said as i sit here today i am fairly certain there is 
wheelerdealering going on within five miles of this building 
bilzerian a highschool dropout and vietnam veteran who capped 
a meteoric business career with the 106 billion takeover of 
singer co was convicted june 9 on nine counts of securities 
fraud conspiracy to commit tax fraud and making false statements 
to the government 
he also was sentenced to two years probation and 250 hours of 
community service for a pattern of lawbreaking in three failed 
takeovers and another stock deal in 1985 and 1986 that netted him 
more than 12 million 
bilzerian had faced a maximum 45 years in prison and 225 
million in fines still his sentence was the longest to date in 
cases derived from the confessions of jailed stock speculator ivan 
boesky who is serving a threeyear term 
the lure of money has caused him an intelligent young man 
to lose what i perceive to be proper perspective ward said in 
short he lies 
the charges involved raids on apparel maker cluett peabody amp 
co building supplies maker hh robertson amp co and hammermill 
paper co and another transaction of armco inc stock 
bilzerian plans to appeal said his attorney arthur f mathews 
my trial and conviction has publicly humiliated me and i am 
sorry for any sorrow and shame i have caused my family and 
friends bilzerian stated in a presentencing letter to ward i 
wish i could turn back the clock of time and correct whatever 
mistakes i may have made 
bilzerian was freed on bail pending appeal but ward ordered 
bilzerian who in july reported a net worth of 814 million to 
pay the fines within 30 days 
none of the charges against bilzerian involved his 1988 takeover 
of singer the sewingmachine maker turned defense contractor 
the bilzerian conviction was the first jury verdict in the 
governments continuing whitecollar corruption probe which began 
with the may 1986 arrest of former trader dennis levine who led 
investigators to boesky 
bilzerian was convicted of submitting false documents to the 
securities and exchange commission filing false tax returns and 
rigging transactions to skirt federal tax and disclosure laws in 
tandem with los angeles stockbroker boyd l jefferies who 
testified against bilzerian 
jefferies who testified against bilzerian recently received a 
suspended sentence sentencing is pending for others including six 
former princetonnewport partners lp defendants found guilty of 
fraud and racketeering and former drexel burnham lambert inc 
managing director martin a siegel 
bilzerian who resigned as singer chairman in june still faces 
civil securities charges filed by the sec seeking 313 million in 
alleged illegal profits 
assistant us attorney david brodsky cited bilzerians alleged 
arrogance and utter disregard for the law said bilzerian 
committed perjury during the trial and said a lengthy prison term 
would deter similar behavior on wall street 
the case was the first criminal trial of illegal stock 
parking in which securities ownership is disguised to dodge 
federal tax or disclosure laws 
over an 18month period bilzerian committed serious securities 
crimes over and over again brodsky said 
mathews sought a suspended sentence on the grounds that 
bilzerian was a firsttime offender that his prosecution was a 
novelty that his crimes had no identifiable victims and that 
deterrence had been achieved 
